Prague Public Transportation (MHD) will introduce the chip in their ticket system on Wednesday
On Wednesday 1 October 2008 the first passengers will be registered in the history of the Pražský Dopravní podnik (the Prague Transport Agency) as the date on which the first passengers will arrive in the metro, tram and bus, who, instead of having a paper ticket, will have an electronic coupon in their pocket.
Currently, the latter is accessible to approximately a hundred thousand people, owners of the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can purchase a 30 day or 90 day coupon (this will be valid from 1 January 2009) and at the same time make it registered on their chip card in the information points and offices of the Dopravní podnik (the Transport Agency), located in the metro stations Muzeum, Můstek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
From yesterday, there is also the possibility to buy the coups via the internet on the web pages of the Dopravní podnik: www.dpp.cz.
More than 400 people took advantage of the service in the morning.
Those who will begin to use the online store can definitely forget the boxes in the metro stations, where they had so far to walk with impatience in long ribs in order to get paper tickets.
In fact, they will buy their coupon via the internet and it will be recorded on their Opencard card in one of the thirteen Městská knihovna (municipal libraries).
"In these contact points, there is available to passengers a container with a trained staff, which will help those interested with the online purchase and, in addition, will record the coupon they bought on their card," said project spokesman Martin Opatrný.
In addition to the libraries, it will also be possible to record electronic coupons on the Opencard in automatic distributors installed in the vestibule of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, remind the machines to compose the tickets and passengers may have already noticed them at the metro stations Roztyly, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year, there should be eighty," Opatrný added.
An automatic will control the coupon instead of the driver
The machines that will work from tomorrow are easy to use.
Just enter the Opencard chip card and the previously purchased coupon will be registered on the card itself.
