It should discourage drivers from fast driving and alcohol at driving.
But also remind them to take the belt before starting.
It mainly wants to touch the consciousness of young drivers, motorists, pedestrians, without forgetting professional drivers.
What will appear in the spots?
Especially personal stories that will attack emotions.
This is also the “bloody” slogan of the entire campaign:
You don’t think – you pay.
The phrase "You don't think" is inserted in majuscules on the registration board.
Then, in a blade of blood, there is the phrase "You will pay."
This must symbolize that one can pay for life a moment of negligence.
The spots will "hunt" the spectators until 2010.
The ministry was inspired by similar campaigns in the Anglo-Saxon countries, where you can commonly see images with drastic images of the victims of the accidents.
