Questions that arise after the accident: Are stewards in the car illegal?
The law ignores them; walking in a long distance car is prohibited
In the context of the tragic bus accident of the Student Agency company near Padua, Italy, the question arises whether stewards and passengers can during the journey move inside the bus.
"If we wanted to comply with the law strictly and formally, the activity of a steward is contrary to the road traffic law," said transport ministry spokesman Karel Hanzelka.
The incident, during which a 22-year-old hostess died, was apparently caused by the driver of a truck that crossed the bus road.
The girl was unfortunately sitting next to the driver, on the vehicle’s most dangerous seat, although she has two other seats at her disposal.
But the bus can have an accident, or even brake suddenly, also when the steward serves the coffee or distributes the newspapers.
What matters is whether the bus is in accordance with its technical list equipped with standing places or not.
If this standing seat equipment is not approved, passengers must stay sitting.
The long-distance Student Agency buses have no standing places; this was confirmed at Aktuálně.cz by the company director Radim Jančura.
“This is a matter that we have dealt with with the ministry and, at the beginning, it prohibits any travel of passengers.
Then they canceled it and we got that passengers can go to the toilets during the trip provided they have their own seat," he revealed his position.
The law ignores the steward.
"There is no univocal legal interpretation of the role of steward - no legal prescription takes care of this role.
On the other hand, no legal prescription does not prohibit the carrier from offering services either.
The road transport law only knows the term vehicle recipient; it does not define its rights and duties," said spokesman Hanzelka with more ambiguity.
Josef Pokorný, the Director of the Department of Road Vehicle Traffic, believes, on the contrary, that the law addresses the problem sufficiently.
“All depends on whether the bus has in its approval the permission to offer standing places.
Everything lies in it,” he says.
The buses are divided into urban places, where there are standing places and a limited maximum speed, interurban places with standing places and a higher permitted speed and in long distance buses without standing places with the highest permitted maximum speed and seats equipped with safety belt.
As in the aircraft, an expert says.
Jaroslav Hořín, an expert at BESIP (Road Traffic Safety) in Transportation Safety, does not see the shipping of stewards on board as a major problem.
"With regular traffic, there is no danger. the situation can be compared to that of service in aircraft.
Neither, it’s uncertain when turbulence will happen and the air host can kick the head.”
“But if the bus would have stopped suddenly, the laws of physics would obviously be valid.
The same way as in a city bus or in a tram.
The carrier must manage the safety of the stewards by internal requirements," he says and also believes that from the point of view of the law, the problem is not solved.
Jančura is ready to remove these services
Student Agency is the only bus carrier offering stewards services.
He employs two hundred.
Even after this accident, the director does not consider their profession as a risky profession.
However, as soon as I get the impression that it is a risky business, I will remove it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and journal on board.
This will also reduce the costs,” he said.
The safety concern is the reason that gives to the absence of stewards in its vehicles the director of the Asiana Alexei Litvine, who provides, compared to SA, a very small number of lines.
“We don’t have any hosts, we’re opposed from the beginning.
Sooner or later it will end with a deadly accident," he said, a year ago, at Týden.cz.
A huge tragedy has happened.
A young host from the Plzeň region, who worked for the company for two years, died in the crash on the Naples line.
A Slovene truck probably left the emergency stop band without using a flash and it blocked the road to the bus.
The driver of the latter to try to avoid it through a sudden maneuver, but he broke it by his right side.
Jančura refuses that the two seats reserved for the rest of the stewards were sold.
"In the case of long-distance lines, it is not possible to book these seats, they are blocked."
The company plans to file a complaint against the truck driver.
For the compensation of the girl’s family, the agency will not wait for the judgment of the court, but in terms of financial compensation, it also count on the guilty.
A change to the law?
Not in sight
A amendment to the law, which is being drawn up, for more than a year, by a group of thirty experts from the Ministry of Transport, could bring details about the shifts of the stewards on board the bus.
“But it has not reached any conclusion on this issue.
Indeed, she is not too interested in the buses, but rather the point system, the maximum speed on the highway and the use of the mobile on the wheel,” says the expert Hořín.
“The Ministry of Transport does not consider the activities of the stewards as something that would fundamentally put the safety of passengers in danger,” said spokesman Hanzelka, pointing out that the safety control of buses is under the authority of the police and the Office for Safety at Work.
