The first time that happens it may surprise you, but in reality it doesn’t matter.
This is a benign sleep alteration that is called sleepy.
This is quite common, especially in children and adolescents.
There are more than one people who talk during the night.
This phenomenon can appear very sporadically (one time in life, for example, associated with an episode of severe fever), or more periodically (to every day, once a week, once a month ...), the day after the child no longer remembers anything.
There is no single cause that determines its appearance.
They are often linked to other sleep disorders such as nightmares, night terrors, night enuresis (pipe in bed) or sleepambulism, but that’s not always the case.
As we have already said before, they can also be associated with very strong fever, situations of stress or exaggeration.
This is a little studied phenomenon.
The intensity with which it occurs is also very variable.
It may be that he speaks with a small quiet voice, with isolated words, murmures or, on the contrary, with screams, crying, long speeches...
In the case where sleepy disease becomes very common, it would be reasonable to observe the child and consult a specialist, to check if there is a problem that causes a lot of anxiety and in order to get an explanation for this problem.
We said that this is a beneficial alteration, therefore there is no treatment, unless it is associated with another sleep alteration that can be treated (for example, if it is associated with sleep apnea or stress).
What can be done is to take into account a number of very simple preventive measures such as:
Try not to excite the child before going to sleep.
Therefore, look for quiet games and avoid programs or TV series that are more or less violent.
With very nervous children who have trouble relaxing, relaxation techniques can be used to help them calm inside.
This will allow the child to have a more peaceful sleep.
As soon as the sleeps appear, try to stay calm.
Remember that they are harmless for the child and that the next day he will no longer remember what happened.
useful advice
Do not wake him up.
This is unnecessary because he is unconscious and you would wake him up.
Even if he speaks, he sleeps and then rests.
Remember that if he is very anxious several times, it is advisable to consult a doctor or check what causes so much anxiety in the child.
If you understand what he says (which is not usual), don’t have the temptation to ask him to get information.
You won’t get anything, because while sleeping, he is not conscious to be able to organize his thought.
In addition, you will hear what he says, but you won’t know what he is dreaming about, then pay attention to how you will interpret the information and the conclusions you draw from it.
Never tell the child that you can ask him during the night to know his secrets.
Not even by joking.
This causes a lot of anxiety.
In conclusion, don’t worry, it’s nothing bad, it’s an episode that lasts just a few minutes.
